clusterList.phrase: feith's team it turned out had been sifting through raw intelligence and wanted to brief us on things they thought we had missed trouble was while they seem to like playing the role of analysts they showed none of the professional skills or discipline required fieth and company would find little nuggets that supported their beliefs and seize upon them never understanding that there might be a larger picture that they were missing isolated data points became so important to them that they would never look at the thousands of other data points that might convey an opposite story
